texts.text: *Yell*
Finally, I won—
>After defeating Kokoro's demon, his final obstacle—
>Period briefly drops his guard, and the victor is decided.
! Kokoroooo!
It's over, Period.
Damn it..!. Damn, damn, damn, damn! I was so close!!
I lost again?! I have to watch my promised world disappear?!
Curse you... Curse you...!
I beat the humans, yet the Dragon Stream screwed me over...!
You're wrong.
In what way...?
I never could have won on my own.
If a bit less optimism had entered the Stream, I would've lost.
However, everyone's hopeful thoughts gave me strength.
That's why I could go all out and summon that demon.
One person's positivity can't change the world,
but I had support from all over Tokyo, Japan, and the world.
That's why you lost to me.
You lost to humans and the fellowship between them.
...That fellowship...really is a pain in my ass...
Period. ...No, Marduk.
It's time to end this. This world isn't yours to control.
...Yeah, you're right. I'm finished.
I can tell my body is too exhausted to fight.
It's weird to say, though, since I'm only made up of data.
You, too, tried to protect this world from malice,
but wasn't your goal also to conquer it?
Yeah... I guess so...
I won't let the denizens of Hell have their way.
This world belongs to everyone living in it!
...You may be right. However—
Human or not, handing over this world that's rightfully mine,
still kinda pisses me off...!
Shoot!
>Period musters one final attack and pierces Kokoro!
Agh!
(I messed up! I thought he couldn't fight back anymore—)
Hahaha! Can you stop the flow of malice now with those wounds?
Period!
Later, Dragon Stream Priestess. Don't struggle too much.
I'll watch over everyone's demise from Hell...
>Although Kokoro had subdued the malice until that point...
>Due to the summons and Period's attack, Kokoro—
>No longer has the strength to hold it back.
Oh no...! The malice is...!
At this rate, the world will...!
>Despite her best efforts, evil floods into the Dragon Stream.
Stop...! STOOOOOOP!!
>The stream continues relentlessly.
Please... I beg you...!
>Her pleas are in vain as the Dragon Stream is contaminated.
Hey! How's Kokoro?! What happened to her?!
I'm not sure... Period's signal vanished, but...
...Unfortunately, we can't peek into the Dragon Stream.

All we can do is hope she's safe.
Agh?!
What the?! An earthquake?!
Tch, it's a big one. Plus—
It's loooong!!
It's still going! This isn't a normal quake!
At any rate, let's get out of here or we'll be buried alive!
Is-Is it over...?
That lasted for almost five minutes.
What's goin' on today...? There was a weird song, then—
*Growl*
What is that?! A dog?!
*Roar*
*Shout*
*Howl*
What?
Fear not. Mankind will survive even if this world is destroyed.
Th-There are monsters here, too! Eeeeek!!
Don't resist. We have no wish to harm you.
But should you try to escape—
*Shout*
We won't hesitate to take a limb or two.

My leg...! My leeeeeeg...!
*Scream*
It...disappeared...?
What is this? Is this reality...?
It...can't be...
Normal people can see demons now?!
It's like when the leftover Acolytes polluted the Dragon Stream.
No, it seems worse than that...
The Dragon Stream has never been this contaminated...
Wait, does that mean—
Our "badass" plan failed...?
Oh no... It has awakened...
Vanitas...!
It...can't be...
